      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAROLINE BANNER (7) box seated off the lead and kept coming to win (26.72) at Bulli in Grade 5 over 472m. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from an outside draw. Makes plenty of appeal if runs up to latest. HARD SNIFF STYLE (1) hit the frame two on end before getting off the mark with a deserved win last time, scoring at this track over 520m (29.95). Ran the fastest time on the program in his latest win. Can go close again if runs up to latest figure. NO SHAME (2) was safely held last time out, finishing fifth at Gosford over 515m behind Status Jewel (30.04) in a Grade 5. Was in the money prior to that. Some good form is emerging from her last run. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. FLASHBACK JIM (5) is last start winner who looks one of the chances.",
